PET Studies of Phonological Processing: A Critical Reply to Poeppel Poeppel (1996) raises a number of criticisms about the methods and reported results for eight studies of phonological processing from six different neuroimaging laboratories. We would freely admit that valid criticisms of PET methodology can be made and that, like any method, it has limitations in fact, we and others have engaged in such critical commentary (Steinmetz & Seitz, 1991